reviews.text: Atmosphere is great, only tried the Mac N Cheese and tbh it was one of the best I‚Äôve ever had. Good location and the bartenders know how to make a good Long Island.

Pretty decent first experience. Staff was friendly and quick to come over. Onion petals were delicious. The only reason I took a star off was because I asked for crispy wings and the wings were still rubbery. Would try a second time but not for the wings. Still a good experience.
**update over a year later. Upped to five stars for the flavor of food and quality. Way better food this time around! Can't wait to come back and try something new!

All the bartenders were very friendly and efficient. Gia was so sweet. We went in to watch the Phillies game and had a good time and good food. The Italian steam clams, seared tuna, and fried shrimp platter were delicious. Allen, I forgot the delicious homemade potato chips. We will be back soon.

Excellent food and excellent service. First time trying this restaurant. The waitress was super friendly and knowledgeable about the items on the menu. Some appetizers are half price during the late afternoon/early evening hours. Our food came out quick and everything was delicious. Definitely recommend giving this place a shot if you're in the area and looking for some good food (especially the burgers).
Love Sidelines! Their wings and fries are the best! Always awesome service and Bella is very accommodating and always so helpful!
